A student of the Yobe State University, Damaturu, Maryam Lawan Goroma on Thursday, slumped and died shortly after writing her examination. A classmate of the deceased, Bukar Maisandari who disclosed this on his Facebook account said that the deceased suddenly collapsed and was confirmed dead shortly. He posted, “Innaa Lillaahi Wa Innaa Ilaihir Raaji’uun. I received with a heavy heart the news of the sudden death of our classmate Maryam Lawan Goroma. “She was healthy and hearty until today afternoon when she suddenly collapsed and was confirmed death shortly. “May Almighty Allah forgive her shortcomings. May Al-Jannah Firdausi be her final abode. “My deepest sympathy to her family and friends and to all my Chemical [Engineering] colleagues. “May Allah give you comfort to bear this loss. Ameen.”‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒